<p>I am uisng rails 3 and the steps that I have done</p>  <ol> <li><p>rails new MeBay</p></li> <li><p>rails g model ad name:string description:text price:decimal seller_id:integer email:string imr_url:string</p></li> <li><p>rake db:migrate</p></li> <li><p>rails generate controller ads</p></li> <li><p>show.html.erb</p>  <pre><code>&lt;html&gt; &lt;head&gt;   &lt;title&gt; &lt;/title&gt;  &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt; &lt;p&gt;   &lt;b&gt;Name:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;%= @ad.name %&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;  &lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;%= @ad.description %&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;  &lt;b&gt;Price:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;%= @ad.price %&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;  &lt;b&gt;Seller Id:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;%= @ad.seller_id %&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;  &lt;b&gt;Email:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;%= @ad.email %&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;  &lt;img src="&lt;%= @ad.img_url %&gt;"/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre></li> <li><p>config/routes.rb</p>  <pre><code>controller 'ads' do        match 'ads/:id' =&gt; :show match 'ads/:id' =&gt; :index end </code></pre></li> <li><p>ads_controller</p>  <pre><code>def show   @ad = Ad.find(params[:id]) end def index   @ads = Ad.find(:all) end </code></pre></li> <li><p>index.html.erb</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>    &lt;h1&gt;All ads&lt;/h1&gt;     &lt;ul&gt;        &lt;% for ad in @ads %&gt;        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href ="/ads/&lt;%= ad.id %&gt;"&gt;&lt;%= ad.name %&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;        &lt;% end %&gt;     &lt;/ul&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p></li> </ol>  <p>after starting the rails server </p>  <p>in browser I am trying</p>  <pre><code>http://localhost:3000/show/ads/3 </code></pre>  <p>I am getting routing error. Please help on solving this error.</p>